summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2006 LINCOLN ZEPHYR. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE DASHBOARD WAS WARPED. THE MIDDLE OF THE DASHBOARD TOWARDS THE WINDSHIELD, WHERE THE DEFROST VENTS WERE LOCATED, WERE NOT FITTING CORRECTLY. THE CONTACT ALSO STATED THAT A RUBBER PIECE WAS PARTIALLY COVERING THE VENTS. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT TAKEN TO AN INDEPENDENT MECHANIC OR LOCAL DEALER FOR DIAGNOSTIC TESTING. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOT MADE AWARE OF THE ISSUE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS UNKNOWN.
